# ‚úÖ **1. Brute Force**

Try all possible permutations of cities.

* Number of possible tours: ((n-1)!)
* **Time Complexity:**
  [
  O(n!)
  ]

---

# ‚úÖ **2. Dynamic Programming ‚Äî Held-Karp Algorithm**

Uses bitmask DP to reduce work dramatically.

* **Time Complexity:**
  [
  O(n^2 \cdot 2^n)
  ]
* **Space Complexity:**
  [
  O(n \cdot 2^n)
  ]

‚û°Ô∏è This is the fastest known exact solution.

---

# ‚úÖ **3. Approximation / Heuristics**

These don‚Äôt guarantee the optimal answer but run faster.

### **Nearest Neighbor Heuristic**

* **Time Complexity:**
  [
  O(n^2)
  ]

### **Christofides Algorithm** (for metric TSP)

* **Time Complexity:**
  [
  O(n^3)
  ]
* Guaranteed ‚â§ 1.5√ó optimal.

